## SS 2b. Extract Article Content (after navigating to article page)

Returns the article title and body text. Run this BEFORE reacting or typing a comment. Use the returned `title` and `body` to inform your comment — your comment MUST directly address this specific article's topic.

```javascript
browser.act({
  kind: "evaluate",
  fn: `async () => {
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 3000));
    var h1 = document.querySelector('h1');
    var title = h1 ? h1.innerText.trim() : '';
    var article = document.querySelector('#article-body') || document.querySelector('article');
    var body = article ? article.innerText.trim().slice(0, 500) : '';
    return { title, body };
  }`,
  profile: "{{browser_profile}}"
})
```

