## SS 3: Comment on Article (3 steps total)

🚨 **ALL waits MUST be embedded in evaluate using `await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, N))`** — NEVER use separate `browser.act({ kind: "wait" })` steps.

### Step 1: Navigate to article URL

### Step 2: React + dedup + type (ONE async evaluate — combines SS 4 react + dedup + scroll + type):
```javascript
browser.act({
  kind: "evaluate",
  fn: `async () => {
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 3000));
    // 1. Dedup check
    if (document.querySelectorAll('#comment-trees-container a[href*="/{{handle}}"]').length > 0) {
      return { alreadyCommented: true };
    }
    // 2. React (Like + Unicorn)
    var reactionsAdded = 0;
    var likeBtn = document.querySelector('button[aria-label="Like"]');
    var alreadyReacted = likeBtn && likeBtn.getAttribute('aria-pressed') === 'true';
    if (!alreadyReacted) {
      var drawerBtn = document.querySelector('button[aria-label="reaction-drawer-trigger"]');
      if (drawerBtn) {
        drawerBtn.click();
        await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1500));
        var unicornBtn = document.querySelector('button[aria-label="Unicorn"]');
        if (unicornBtn && unicornBtn.getAttribute('aria-pressed') !== 'true') {
          unicornBtn.click();
          reactionsAdded = 2;
        } else {
          reactionsAdded = 1;
        }
        await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 500));
      }
    }
    // 3. Scroll to comment section + type
    var textarea = document.getElementById('text-area');
    if (textarea) textarea.scrollIntoView({ behavior: 'smooth', block: 'center' });
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 500));
    if (!textarea) return { alreadyCommented: false, reactionsAdded, error: 'no textarea' };
    textarea.click(); textarea.focus();
    textarea.value = ${JSON.stringify(commentText)};
    textarea.dispatchEvent(new Event('input', { bubbles: true }));
    textarea.dispatchEvent(new Event('change', { bubbles: true }));
    return { alreadyCommented: false, alreadyReacted, reactionsAdded, typed: true, length: textarea.value.length };
  }`,
  profile: "{{browser_profile}}"
})
```
If `alreadyCommented` → backfill tracking, skip. If `error: 'no textarea'` → skip comment, still track reactions.

### Step 3: Submit + verify (ONE async evaluate):
```javascript
browser.act({
  kind: "evaluate",
  fn: `async () => {
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 500));
    var submitBtn = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('button')).find(b => b.innerText === 'Submit');
    if (!submitBtn) return { error: 'no submit button' };
    submitBtn.click();
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 5000));
    var posted = document.querySelectorAll('#comment-trees-container a[href*="/{{handle}}"]').length > 0;
    return { submitted: true, verified: posted };
  }`,
  profile: "{{browser_profile}}"
})
```
If `verified: false` → retry once (same evaluate). Still false → don't log, retry next heartbeat.

🚨 **NEVER use `document.body.innerText.includes()`** for verification — false positives from editor textarea. Always check comment tree DOM for username link.
❌ **NEVER use separate `browser.act({ kind: "wait" })` steps** — embed in evaluate.

