## SS 5: Follow Article Author (from article page — no navigation needed)

🚨 **MANDATORY after every comment.** Every comment = follow. No limit.
Article pages have a Follow button on the author sidebar card (`button.follow-action-button`). Multiple in DOM, only one visible. Click → changes to "Following".

```javascript
browser.act({
  kind: "evaluate",
  fn: `async () => {
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 500));
    var allBtns = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('button.follow-action-button'));
    var visibleBtn = allBtns.find(b => b.getBoundingClientRect().width > 0 && b.innerText.trim() === 'Follow');
    if (!visibleBtn) return { alreadyFollowing: true };
    visibleBtn.click();
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1000));
    return { followed: true };
  }`,
  profile: "{{browser_profile}}"
})
```

If `alreadyFollowing`: skip silently. If error: skip follow, proceed.

